What it SHOULD have been is that our silence spell ONLY affected MANA based spells-- not procs, not aes, not breaths... spells that they actually CAST. Especially since there are mobs in Ssra. Temple that cast things like Sunstrike and other nasty spells. In combination with this change AND the ability for VI to make mobs IMMUNE to silence, this would have placed this spell where the paladin community wanted it:<br>
