<br>
First off, YES, the spell was overpowered.<br>
<br>
4 paladins could trivialize any dragon encounter.  Dragon's don't generally melee very well, and count on (a) FEAR and (b) NASTY AEs to make them challenging.<br>
<br>
This was eliminated by this spell.  Sad to say, it was very endgame-unbalancing.  I accept that :)  Adding a long recast time (2+ minutes?) would have fixed the problem, or finding a way to flag some mobs immune to silence.  I actually beleive that this change is temporary, while they work on a better solution, and that the silence effect will be back &quot;soon&quot;.<br>
<br>
As the spell stands now, it's shit - its not a Mana tap even - we don't GAIN 100 mana by casting it, just lose the 75 it costs to cast.  And leaving 18 sec recast is a joke.  Clearly they said &quot;oh shit&quot; and picked a new effect to push out ASAP, without looking at anything else.<br>
<br>
HOnestly, change the spell to costing 1 mana and a 7 second recast, and it becomes useful again.  A lot of encounters involve seiving, and paladins would be able to help there.  As it stands now, its useless.  I have hope they'll fix that.<br>
<br>
Regarding Merton's babble about paladins being useless, I'm gonna take the bait.  At one point, hybrids (both SK and paladins, and to a lesser extent, rangers) had fallen WAY behind.  Pal/SK damage output was crap, and tanking ability was even worse.  Oh, and spells were useless.  Those that stuck it out anyway learned to find other ways to be useful.<br>
<br>
Now, upgrade paladin/SK tanking.  If not for the defensive discipline, they'd be just about equal to warriors (i know, not quite as good, but its only the discipline that makes warriors the ONLY choice for tanks).  Merton, if you're ever lucky enough to get to go on a large NToV raid or something (no, watching while you FD to PoM doesn't count), keep an eye on what we do with adds.  Watch the paladins/sk's in particular.<br>
<br>
Now, upgrade paladin/SK damage output.  If we could dual wield, we'd be equal to warriors - completely.  As it stands now, at 60, we're what, 5% behind warriors, 8% behind rangers, and about 20% behind monks (if i remember correctly).  However, that assumes everyone lives the entire fight.<br>
<br>
Monks spend so much time in FD, that 20% is negated.  If they DON'T drop to the floor or otherwise evade aggro, they get hit.  Monks getting hit by ubermobs = LOADING, PLEASE WAIT... and again... no 20% advantage.<br>
<br>
Not a pal vs monk war here by any means - monks do more damage when played well, for sure, but after they pull, they just represent another 40-60 DPS on a raid - just like a paladin or SK.  And while the SK can also pull just as well, the paladin can heal (not the main tank but fight in NToV and watch what happens when those wurms.. you know.. breathe... to the other people's HP...)<br>
<br>
So you're pulling and then you're doing damage.  We're doing (roughly the same) damage and healing.  Exactly where are you so much more valuable?<br>
<br>
